  "body": "Currently kubectl has logic to apply partial updates to resources. This responsibility logically seems like it should belong to the CRUD rest server. More concretely, if this responsibility is moved into the apiserver, it would allow clients that use the api directly to benefit from this feature. An obvious interface would be to follow [RFC7368](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7386) and implement resources that respond to requests with HTTP `PATCH` method and `Content-Type: application/merge-patch+json`.\n",
